MEASUREMENTS (
MM
). N = one male or two females, mean (range). Length of body: male 23.2, female 19.35 (18.0–20.7); length of fore wing: male 27.1, female 25.40 (24.5–26.3); width of fore wing: male 9.2, female 8.50 (8.1–8.9); length of head: male 3.7, female 3.53 (3.45–3.6); width of head including eyes: male 8.5, female 7.95 (7.6–8.3); width of pronotum including suprahumeral plates: male 7.75, female 7.10 (6.7–7.5); width of mesonotum: male 6.4, female 5.83 (5.6–6.05).
